I have the same problems as angelmartin.  I followed the instructions and got the "thank you for activating" message, but after that the program would not open.

found different instructions online which said to press '+' next to Reset, then change Year to 'B933'.  After that it said to select Basic version then click Generate.  This also said the program was activated, but I still had the same problem with the program not launching.

I also could get the program activated but it would not launch.  Instead I followed these instructions and it worked.  Make sure when you uninstall you also delete folder C:ProgramDataIntuit Canadatt2012 before reinstalling.

Year codes 
	2010 - B935
	2011 - B934
	2012 - B933



Turbo Tax 20 Canadian Version
(previously QuickTax)

Includes 20 returns

NOTE:
This download is clean.
The Keygen may get flagged as a virus and/or malware.
Any AV flag is a false-positive. That is the nature of the beast.

Administrative privileges may be required.


Begin install (Offline)
During installation, Select 'I do not agree to transmit...'

After install is finished, start Turbo Tax

The 'Enter Installation Key' window will appear.

Open the Keygen

Click on the '+' button on the right of the 'Reset' button.

A'Debug' interface will slide up.

Replace Year with 'B933'


Click the 'Generate' button.

The Installation Key should now have been automatically filled into the 'Enter Installation Key' window.
(If not, copy/paste the numbers from the Keygen (6 boxes on the right)

Click on the 'Next' button in the 'Enter Installation Key' window.

The next window is 'Choose Activation Method'

Select 'Automated Telephone Activation', then the 'Next' button.

Now you are at the 'Automated Telephone Activation' window.

Copy/paste the Activation code numbers from the Keygen (5 boxes on the right) into "Your Activation Code' boxes.

You can restore your internet connection.

You can register now, and update the program.
I've registered Turbo Tax, and used the updates feature several times without any problems.

Unless something changes, we're good to go.
